Money Facts
14 Kids are expensive, just observe the world
13 it is not embarrassing to ask for a promotion- improve your professional skills or change your job. Dont assume that Promotion will fix everything
12 it is more profitable to rent than own ~ mortgage bank interest tax for house
11 invest in your health and education
10 dont invest in sth you dont know well
09 dont borrow to pay old debts - no credit card
08 stay connected with your friends and meet new people. Personal relationship is more important than money
07 it is more efficient to buy good quality shoes n clothes. It costs more but in long term works
06 avoid impulse purchases
05 start saving money for old age now
04 eat and cook at home for long term cheaper
03 put part of your salary into a savings account for a rainy day. Life is unpredictable
02 be on the same page with your significant other when it comes to finances. Family budget with your partner
01 find a passive source of income. Study invest money for future

Money facts II
01. The rich pay themselves first
02. The rich base their decisions on long term rewards rather than instant grafication. To actively do what excited you
03. Rich people have several sources of income (mostly passive, without having to physically be there)
04. Rich people continuously invest in themselves (improving yourselves instead of overpriced house)
05. The poor's income only increase in the same rate as inflation, but the rich focuses his energy on what he can control. The rich never blames but take full responsibility for their failures
06. The rich is more excited to be productive and make progress that the rich dont sleep in unlike the poor who sees sleep as a pleasure
07. The rich has got a major purpose, dont see work as a sacrifice. Addicted to the progress unlike the poor have entertainment such as netflix. The rich have a clear vision or purpose.
08. Check list to task that the rich make progress before entertainment such as netflix

